    "Memory allocation\n",
    "-----------------\n",
    "\n",
    "Since nanodisort reflects the CDISORT interface with barely any changes, that means that it is up to the user to trigger memory allocation for the input fields. To do so, we first have to assign sizes to all dimensions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "baaa5334-e0ff-455c-9804-d2369d9485b0",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-01-28T15:36:16.811669Z",
